article.headline: Wis.-Milwaukee 61, Youngstown St. 39
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Paige Paulsen scored 16 points to lead Wis.-Milwaukee to a 61-39 win over Youngstown State on Monday night. The Panthers (8-7, 3-2 Horizon), who have won five-straight games, limited Youngstown State to just 24.5 percent shooting from the field and forced 19 turnovers. Jack Liles had 11 points for the Penguins (6-8, 2-2). The loss snapped the Penguins' three-game winning streak. Deonte Roberts, Ricky Franklin, Allan Hanson and Deion James each added eight points for the Panthers, who won despite shooting just 33.9 percent.
